@Node "EDIT COMMAND" "userman.guide/EDIT COMMAND"
@Next "EXIT"
@Prev "Commands"
@Toc "Commands"

EDIT COMMAND
------------

`EDIT COMMAND' HISTORY-NUMBER

The edit command command lets you edit the specified command using the
editor specified by the EDITOR variable.


@EndNode

@Node "EXIT" "userman.guide/EXIT"
@Next "HISTORY"
@Prev "EDIT COMMAND"
@Toc "Commands"

EXIT
----

`EXIT'

The exit command will exit you from the command shell.  All open tables
will be closed for you when you exit.

If you have an open cursor, you will receive an error message and the
program will not exit.


@EndNode

@Node "HISTORY" "userman.guide/HISTORY"
@Next "SET"
@Prev "EXIT"
@Toc "Commands"

HISTORY
-------

`HISTORY'

The history command displays a list of the history buffer.  Each entry
consists of the history number and the command text.


@EndNode

@Node "SET" "userman.guide/SET"
@Next "SYSTEM"
@Prev "HISTORY"
@Toc "Commands"

SET
---

`SET' [ VARIABLE-NAME = VARIABLE-VALUE ]

The set command lets you store values in command shell variables that
can be used later.  If the arguments to set are omitted, a listing of
all variables and values is produced.


@EndNode

@Node "SYSTEM" "userman.guide/SYSTEM"
@Next "VERSION"
@Prev "SET"
@Toc "Commands"

SYSTEM
------

`SYSTEM' SYSTEM-COMMAND

The system command allow you to execute a system command, such as `dir'
or `ls', without having to leave SQLdb.


@EndNode

@Node "VERSION" "userman.guide/VERSION"
@Prev "SYSTEM"
@Toc "Commands"

VERSION
-------

`VERSION'

The version command displays the current version and any other
pertinent information.


@EndNode

@Node "Server Mode" "userman.guide/Server Mode"
@Prev "Command Shell"
@Toc "Main"

Server mode
***********

When started up in Server Mode, SQLdb will open up an ARexx port called
`SQLserver' and await commands from the port.


 @{" ExecSQL " Link "ExecSQL"} 
 @{" ShutdownSQL " Link "ShutdownSQL"} 
 @{" GetLastCode " Link "GetLastCode"} 
 @{" GetLastErrMsg " Link "GetLastErrMsg"} 


@EndNode

@Node "ExecSQL" "userman.guide/ExecSQL"
@Next "ShutdownSQL"
@Prev "Server Mode"
@Toc "Server Mode"

ExecSQL
=======

`''`ExecSQL'`'' `''SQL-COMMAND-STRING;`''

`ExecSQL' will send the given command to the interpreter to be executed.
If the command is a fetch from a cursor, the result variable will
contain the fetched row.


@EndNode

@Node "ShutdownSQL" "userman.guide/ShutdownSQL"
@Next "GetLastCode"
@Prev "ExecSQL"
@Toc "Server Mode"

ShutdownSQL
===========

`''`ShutdownSQL'`''

ShutdownSQL will tell SQLdb to close the ARexx port and quit.  The
command will fail if there are any open tables or cursors.


@EndNode

@Node "GetLastCode" "userman.guide/GetLastCode"
@Next "GetLastErrMsg"
@Prev "ShutdownSQL"
@Toc "Server Mode"

GetLastCode
===========

`''`GetLastCode'`''

Will put the result code from the last command into the result variable.


@EndNode

@Node "GetLastErrMsg" "userman.guide/GetLastErrMsg"
@Prev "GetLastCode"
@Toc "Server Mode"

GetLastErrMsg
=============

`''`GetLastErrMsg'`''

Will put the error message from the last command into the result
variable.

@EndNode

